
======================================================================
  Part 1: THE FORBIDDEN SEQUENCE IN ROOT SYSTEMS
======================================================================

Forbidden H values: 7*3^k =  [7, 21, 63, 189, 567, 1701, 5103]

Positive root counts |Phi^+(X_n)|:

Which root systems have |Phi^+| = 7 * 3^k?

  H_forb(k=0) =      7: NONE
  H_forb(k=1) =     21: A_6
  H_forb(k=2) =     63: E_7
  H_forb(k=3) =    189: NONE
  H_forb(k=4) =    567: NONE
  H_forb(k=5) =   1701: NONE

Which root systems have |Phi| = 2 * H_forb(k)?
  2*H_forb(k=0) =     14: NONE
  2*H_forb(k=1) =     42: A_6
  2*H_forb(k=2) =    126: E_7
  2*H_forb(k=3) =    378: NONE
  2*H_forb(k=4) =   1134: NONE
  2*H_forb(k=5) =   3402: NONE

======================================================================
  Part 2: THE FORBIDDEN SEQUENCE AS GAUSSIAN BINOMIALS
======================================================================

Key identity: [n choose 1]_q = (q^n - 1)/(q - 1) = Phi_n(q) (?)
Actually: [n choose 1]_q = 1 + q + q^2 + ... + q^{n-1}

At q = KEY1 = 2:
  [n= 1 choose 1]_2 =      1 = 2^1-1
  [n= 2 choose 1]_2 =      3 = 2^2-1
  [n= 3 choose 1]_2 =      7 = 2^3-1  = H_forb(k=0)
  [n= 4 choose 1]_2 =     15 = 2^4-1
  [n= 5 choose 1]_2 =     31 = 2^5-1
  [n= 6 choose 1]_2 =     63 = 2^6-1  = H_forb(k=2)
  [n= 7 choose 1]_2 =    127 = 2^7-1
  [n= 8 choose 1]_2 =    255 = 2^8-1
  [n= 9 choose 1]_2 =    511 = 2^9-1
  [n=10 choose 1]_2 =   1023 = 2^10-1

PATTERN: H_forb(k) = 7*3^k = [? choose 1]_2
  7 = [3 choose 1]_2 = 2^3 - 1 = M_3
  21 = [? choose 1]_2?  21 = 2^? - 1? No! 2^5-1=31, not 21
  So 21 is NOT [n choose 1]_2 for any n
  But 63 = [6 choose 1]_2 = 2^6 - 1 = M_6 ✓

Forbidden values that are Mersenne numbers 2^n - 1:
  H_forb(k=0) = 7 = 2^3 - 1 = M_3 ✓
  H_forb(k=1) = 21 = NOT Mersenne (2^4.4594 - 1)
  H_forb(k=2) = 63 = 2^6 - 1 = M_6 ✓
  H_forb(k=3) = 189 = NOT Mersenne (2^7.5699 - 1)
  H_forb(k=4) = 567 = NOT Mersenne (2^9.1497 - 1)
  H_forb(k=5) = 1701 = NOT Mersenne (2^10.7330 - 1)
  H_forb(k=6) = 5103 = NOT Mersenne (2^12.3174 - 1)
  H_forb(k=7) = 15309 = NOT Mersenne (2^13.9022 - 1)

Only k=0 (7=M_3) and k=2 (63=M_6) are Mersenne!
  k=0: 7 = 2^3 - 1, exponent 3 = KEY2
  k=2: 63 = 2^6 - 1, exponent 6 = KEY1*KEY2 = h(G2)
  Next would need 7*3^k = 2^m - 1:
  7*3^4 = 567 = 2^? - 1? 2^9=512, 2^10=1024. No.

The pattern: 7*3^k is Mersenne iff 3 * 2^k divides the Mersenne exponent
  k=0: exponent 3 = 3 * 2^0 ✓
  k=2: exponent 6 = 3 * 2^1... wait, that gives k=1 not k=2

  Actually: 7*3^0 = 7 = M_3, 7*3^2 = 63 = M_6
  Exponents 3, 6: ratio = 2 = KEY1
  The Mersenne-forbidden are at k=0 and k=2 (even k only!)

